Blue Inc — Web Challenge Writeup

Challenge Description

Blue Inc is a demo social media website still under construction.
User registration is not yet implemented, but the application provides demo credentials for visitors:

Username: demo
Password: demo

Initial Access

Using the provided credentials, we log in successfully as the demo user and are redirected to the profile page.

Example:

/profile.php?user=demo

The page displays basic user information without any access restrictions.

Vulnerability Identification

While inspecting the profile URL, we notice that the username is controlled entirely via a GET parameter:

profile.php?user=demo

There is no server-side authorization check to verify whether the logged-in user is allowed to view the requested profile.

This indicates an Insecure Direct Object Reference (IDOR) vulnerability.

Exploitation

To test this, we manually modify the user parameter in the URL from demo to admin:

http://cdcamxwl32pue3e6mekgvdm0h9vrq873o8mombwzy-web.cybertalentslabs.com/profile.php?user=admin

Result

The application loads the admin profile page without any authentication or privilege validation.

The flag is displayed directly on the admin profile page.

